# VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)
 
## What is VPC?
A VPC is a private network in AWS where you launch resources like EC2.
 
## Why VPC is used?
- Network isolation
- Security
- Control over IP addressing
 
## Main Components
- VPC
- Subnet (Public / Private)
- Route Table
- Internet Gateway
- NAT Gateway
- NACL
- Security Group

### 📝 Key Points
• A **VPC** is a logically isolated private network in AWS.  
• Public subnet can access the internet through Internet Gateway.  
• Private subnet does not have direct internet access.  
• NAT Gateway allows private subnet instances to access internet (for updates).  
• Route tables define how traffic flows in your network.  
• Security Groups are stateful firewalls at instance level.  
• NACLs are stateless firewalls at subnet level.
 
